Overview:

This guide will show you hwo to 
1. Build an attacker and victim machine and;
2. Build a server to host Wazuh, an open-source SIEM & XDR tool.

I choose to host my Wazuh server through DigitalOcean to save compute power for my attack and victim VMs thay will run on my local host. This guide will walk through the steps of creating a DigitalOcean Droplet (cloud server).
###This will require payment###

You can choose to install Wazuh on an Ubuntu VM that runs on your host machine. The install instructions will be the same

Reference Links
1. https://www.wazuh.com/
2. https://www.digitalocean.com/
3. https://www.kali.org/get-kali/#kali-platforms
4. https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/software-download/windows10

Specifications (at the time of this writing):

Wazuh Server
OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS x64 
8+ GB RAM
50+ GB HDD

Attacker Machine
OS: Kali Linux 2024.3
4+ GB RAM
50+ GB HDD

Victim Machine
OS: Kali Linux 2024.3
4+ GB RAM
50+ GB HDD

Once your DigitalOcean account is created:

1. Select the "Create" dropdown and then select "Droplet"
2. Choose your region & data center 


